<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-6889] CBR - Should break out if exception was thrown when evaluating predicate</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-6889</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If having a CBR and the predicate throws an exception, then the next predicate is called before error handler triggers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should break out when exception is detected like pipeline/multicast can do.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
